			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Job Description</strong><br />
We&rsquo;re looking for innovators and problem solvers who want to have an enormous impact on the world and are passionate about taking on the largest of challenges. Join Grovo&rsquo;s talented engineering team and lead the development of our core product features. You will be a critical member of the team as we build our product and continue expanding to a global audience.</p>
<p>
You will collaborate closely with our team of engineers, developing on the full application stack. We&rsquo;re fast-paced and we iterate quickly, pushing deployments to the live site several times a week on our agile development cycle. You will make an immediate impact by working on our engineering team, in our new office, which was named top 5 startup workplaces in NYC! http://thenextweb.com/insider/2012/12/27/awesome-offices-inside-15-fantastic-startup-workplaces-in-new-york/2/</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re built on the LAMP stack and are hosted on AWS. We&rsquo;ve created several internal tools to automate processes and proprietary features that make us unique in the market. These include custom API integrations with Facebook and Twitter, our homegrown HTML5/Flash video player, a data warehouse built from scratch, and our own content management system built with a MongoDB backend. You&rsquo;ll have an opportunity to work with the latest technologies and contribute to these features.</p>
<p>
<strong>Skills &amp; Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
Essential Functions</p>
<ul>
<li>
Work with our Product team to understand the core functionality and desired user experience for our products</li>
<li>
Work with our Growth team to iterate on the site in order to optimize our signup funnels and viral mechanics</li>
<li>
Collaborate with our front-end and backend engineers to develop full end-to-end features</li>
<li>
Run unit tests and take ownership of your code, maintaining and updating it as necessary</li>
<li>
Work within our fast-paced agile development process, releasing smaller updates as part of our daily Scrum and larger deployments within our weekly sprint cycles</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
Job Qualifications</p>
<ul>
<li>
You have several years experience working with PHP in an MVC framework</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;ve worked on the full stack of a website
<ul>
<li>
Strong skills (2+ years) in Javascript (we use the JQuery library)</li>
<li>
Strong skills (2+ years) with relational databases and SQL (we use MySQL)</li>
<li>
Ability to write semantic, valid HTML/CSS</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;re cognizant of code performance and can optimize all levels of the application stack
<ul>
<li>
You know how to use memcached efficiently, how to profile database queries and middle layer code, and can identify front-end inefficiencies using browser tools</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
You&rsquo;re knowledgeable with UNIX and source control revision systems</li>
<li>
You aren&rsquo;t afraid to get your hands dirty with new technologies and API&rsquo;s</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
Preferred</p>
<ul>
<li>
Venture-funded start-up experience</li>
<li>
Contributed to open-source projects</li>
<li>
Public portfolio of past and ongoing work</li>
<li>
Knowledgeable of AWS and their cloud hosting services</li>
<li>
Located in NYC or willing to relocate for the right opportunity</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
Personal</p>
<ul>
<li>
Love the web and technology</li>
<li>
Grow a product that helps people and adds value</li>
<li>
Always loves a good challenge</li>
<li>
Self aware with integrity</li>
<li>
Thrive in a fast-paced environment</li>
<li>
Confident and fun</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>About Grovo</strong></p>
<p>
We were the first to provide Internet education to the world.&nbsp; We created Grovo to help the world better use web and mobile apps with short-form video courses. Our mission is to be your trusted source of real-time, high quality updates to the web and mobile products you and your friends use.</p>
<p>
Grovo makes it easy to be more productive in your personal and professional lives. Grovo produces 1-minute videos covering the latest changes to Internet services like Facebook, Evernote, and Google Apps. Grovo maps these updates to the services people use. People are notified in real-time to help them use the services.</p>
<p>
People in 150 countries are using Grovo to save time and become more effective online. From K-12 school districts to 100 of the Fortune 500 companies, Grovo serves professionals and organizations of all sizes with its freemium business model.</p>
<p>
Grovo was founded in 2010 and is a privately held company headquartered in New York City. Grovo has delivered 1 million video lessons and has raised venture financing from some of Silicon Valley&rsquo;s most prestigious investors.</p>
<p>
Grovo employees enjoy great benefits and perks, including health and dental insurance, stock options, free food/drinks, video games, and more - grovo.com/careers</p>
