			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Position: &nbsp;Enterprise Solutions Advisor (Inside Sales)</strong></p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Company Overview</strong></p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for innovators and problem solvers who want to have an enormous impact on the world and are passionate about taking on the largest of challenges.</p>
<p>
Grovo makes it easy to be more productive in your personal and professional lives online. Grovo produces 1-minute videos covering the latest changes to apps and online tools like Facebook, Evernote, and Google Apps. Grovo maps these updates to the services people use. People are notified in real-time to help them use the services.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Grovo&rsquo;s proprietary technology harvests demand about the most immediate questions people have about new features and functionality. Every day, Grovo&rsquo;s in-house team produces short videos covering these updates and delivers them as they&rsquo;re happening. Currently, the library contains over 3,000 video lessons.&nbsp; Each lesson includes a multiple choice quiz, downloadable PDF and time-synced transcript.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
People in 150 countries are using Grovo to save time and become more effective online.&nbsp; From K-12 school districts to 100 of the Fortune 500 companies, Grovo serves professionals and organizations of all sizes with its freemium business model.</p>
<p>
Grovo was founded in 2010 and is a privately held company headquartered in New York City.&nbsp; Grovo has delivered 1 million video lessons and has raised venture financing from some of Silicon Valley&rsquo;s most prestigious investors.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Position Description</strong></p>
<p>
As an Enterprise Solutions Advisor, you will be responsible for establishing and building enduring customer relationships in your specific market segment.&nbsp; The ideal candidate is thoughtful and deliberate in their actions and believes in achieving personal success through customer success.&nbsp; They treat customers and colleagues alike with fairness, trust, and respect; and they work as smart as they do hard.&nbsp; They see opportunity in the face of challenge want to be part of a nimble and fast-growing start-up where change happens daily.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Essential Functions and&nbsp;</strong><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Responsible for presenting, negotiating and implementing enterprise products and services to current and prospective clients.</li>
<li>
Follow up on new leads and referrals resulting from sales and marketing activities.</li>
<li>
Prepare presentations, proposals and sales agreements.</li>
<li>
Identify and resolve client concerns.</li>
<li>
Prepare a variety of status reports, such as activity, pipeline, follow-up, and other engagement metrics.</li>
<li>
Become an expert on each product you cover: communicate the core value of each product, know who&rsquo;s using it and for what they&rsquo;re using it, understand all of its features, and be able to present and demo it to prospective customers.</li>
<li>
Stay up-to-date on Internet trends and news related to the web products we cover, and provide your customers with updates that are relevant to their needs.</li>
<li>
Strong teamwork and interpersonal skills</li>
</ul>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Professional Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2-5 years of corporate sales experience in an educational or SaaS industry (start-up experience preferred)</li>
<li>
Lives in Southern California or is willing to relocate for the right opportunity</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Preferred Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Undergraduate degree from a top 30 university or 20 liberal arts college</li>
<li>
Venture-funded start-up experience</li>
<li>
Proficient in Salesforce.com and Google Apps (Gmail, Calendar, Drive, etc.)</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Personal</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
The ideal candidate:</li>
<li>
Flexible and able to shift needs with the demands of the business.</li>
<li>
Excellent listening, presentation and negotiation skills.</li>
<li>
Ability to foresee trends and react quickly.</li>
<li>
Demonstrate the ability to anticipate and solve practical problems or resolve issues.</li>
<li>
Lives and breathes the Internet</li>
<li>
Loves the start-up lifestyle and culture</li>
<li>
Positive, upbeat attitude</li>
<li>
Has attention to detail</li>
<li>
Takes pride in his or her work</li>
<li>
Is very proactive and solutions-focused</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Compensation</strong><br />
Competitive base salary, variable commission and bonus plan, stock options, free drinks and snacks, health and dental benefits, and video games</p>
<p>
