<strong>Company Overview</strong><br />
We&rsquo;re looking for innovators and problem solvers who want to have an enormous impact on the world and are passionate about taking on the largest of challenges.</p>
<p>
We were the first to provide Internet education to the world.&nbsp; We created Grovo to help the world better use web and mobile apps with short-form video courses.</p>
<p>
Grovo makes it easy to be more productive in your personal and professional lives online. Grovo produces 1-minute videos covering the latest changes to apps and online tools like Facebook, Evernote, and Google Apps. Grovo maps these updates to the services people use. People are notified in real-time to help them use the services.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Grovo&rsquo;s proprietary technology harvests demand about the most immediate questions people have about new features and functionality. Every day, Grovo&rsquo;s in-house team produces short videos covering these updates and delivers them as they&rsquo;re happening. Currently, the library contains over 3,000 video lessons.&nbsp; Each lesson includes a multiple choice quiz, downloadable PDF and time-synced transcript.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
People in 150 countries are using Grovo to save time and become more effective online.&nbsp; From K-12 school districts to 100 of the Fortune 500 companies, Grovo serves professionals and organizations of all sizes with its freemium business model.</p>
<p>
Grovo was founded in 2010 and is a privately held company headquartered in New York City.&nbsp; Grovo has delivered 1 million video lessons and has raised venture financing from some of Silicon Valley&rsquo;s most prestigious investors.</p>
<p>
For more information, please visit: http://www.grovo.com.</p>
<p>
<strong>Position Description</strong><br />
Each Product Analyst is responsible for a portfolio of some of the Internet&rsquo;s most popular web and mobile apps. Coverage ranges from project management and business tools to analytics and advertising platforms. As those web products and mobile apps change, our analysts provide real-time education for people all over the world, in the form of video lessons, text and infographics.</p>
<p>
Product Analysts work closely with our in-house content team of professional video editors, animators, illustrators and designers to produce video lessons and animations.</p>
<p>
<strong>Essential Functions</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Responsible for a portfolio of web products, spanning a variety of topics, such as, business tools, project management software, analytics and advertising platforms.</li>
<li>
Become an expert on each product you cover: communicate the core value of each product, know who&rsquo;s using it and for what they&rsquo;re using it, understand all of its features, and can teach others how to use those features</li>
<li>
Stay up-to-date on Internet trends and news related to the web products you cover, and provide our users real-time education on those updates</li>
<li>
Write informative and engaging copy for video tutorials, blog posts and infographics</li>
<li>
Work side-by-side with professional video editors, animators and illustrators to produce top-quality videos, blog posts, infographics and other educational materials</li>
<li>
Work with our marketing and social media team to write intelligent, engaging and witty &lsquo;How-To,&rsquo; trend and advice articles for internal and external publication</li>
<li>
Strong teamwork and interpersonal skills</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Professional Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2-5 years of professional experience as a research analyst, financial analyst, consultant, or content manager (start-up experience preferred)</li>
<li>
Undergraduate degree from a top 30 university or 20 liberal arts college</li>
<li>
Lives in NYC or is willing to relocate for the right opportunity</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Preferred</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Venture-funded start-up experience</li>
<li>
Proficient in WordPress</li>
<li>
Previous experience writing about the Internet</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Personal</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
The ideal Product Analyst:</li>
<li>
Lives and breathes the Internet</li>
<li>
Loves the start-up lifestyle and culture</li>
<li>
Is an analytical thinker</li>
<li>
Positive, upbeat attitude</li>
<li>
Has great problem solving skills</li>
<li>
Has attention to detail</li>
<li>
Can communicate clearly, concisely and quickly, both verbally and in writing</li>
<li>
Takes pride in his or her work</li>
<li>
Is very proactive and solutions-focused</li>
</ul>
